[[File:Municipal de caracas.jpg|thumb|Teatro Municipal of Caracas]]
The '''Teatro Municipal''' of Caracas is an opera house in Venezuela. It was inaugurated by President [[Antonio Guzmán Blanco|Guzmán Blanco]] in 1881.
It was begun by a French architect and finished by a Venezuelan architect [[Jesús Muñoz Tébar]].

It is one of the oldest opera houses in South America and continues to mount operatic productions.<ref name="uni">{{cite web | url=http://www.eluniversal.com/arte-y-entretenimiento/cultura/150505/operas-y-zarzuelas-regresan-al-teatro-municipal | title=Operas y zarzuelas | work=[[El Universal (Caracas)|El Universal]] | date=2015 | accessdate=17 July 2015}}</ref> However, it is no longer the city's main opera house since
the [[Teresa Carreño Cultural Complex]] opened in the 1980s. The Teatro Municipal is the home of the Municipal Symphony Orchestra of Caracas. 
[[File:Teatro Municipal de Caracas.jpg|thumb|Interior del Teatro Municipal de Caracas, Venezuela.]]

